The scaling governor parameter indicates the actual power scheme of the CPU. The values of this parameters can be: performance, powersave, userspace, ondemand, conservative or interactive. For further details, see the linux kernel documentation.
The device model is used by the manufacturer to uniquely identify its devices.
The system uptime field indicates how long the device is running.
This value should indicate the underlying hardware model of your device. Unfortunately, many manufacturers doesn\'t fill this field correctly or leaves it empty.

A cluster array is a combination of different types of processors that works together as a single processing unit. (a single cluster indicates a single processor). Every cluster indicates the number of cores and its max and min frequency values.
